Customer Data Segmentation and Visualization
A Django-based web application for customer segmentation using clustering algorithms and visualizing the results interactively. This project helps businesses to analyze customer behavior and create targeted marketing strategies.

📂 Project Structure
nginx
Copy
Edit
Customer Data Segmentation and Visualization
│
├── customer_segmentation_new/   # Django project settings
├── softcom/                     # Django application folder
├── db.sqlite3                   # Project database
├── CC GENERAL.csv               # Dataset file
├── manage.py                    # Django management script
└── README.md                    # Project documentation
🚀 Features
Customer Segmentation using clustering techniques

Data visualization of customer groups

Interactive web-based dashboard

User-friendly interface

Scalable project structure

📊 Tech Stack
Backend: Django (Python)

Database: SQLite

Data Analysis: Python (pandas, scikit-learn)

Visualization: Django Templates, matplotlib (if used)

🛠️ Installation and Setup
1. Clone the Repository
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
2. Create Virtual Environment
bash
Copy
Edit
python -m venv venv
3. Activate Virtual Environment
bash
Copy
Edit
# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

# macOS/Linux
source venv/bin/activate
4. Install Dependencies
bash
Copy
Edit
pip install django
# Install additional packages if required (e.g., pandas, matplotlib)
pip install pandas matplotlib scikit-learn
5. Run Database Migrations
bash
Copy
Edit
python manage.py migrate
6. Start the Development Server
bash
Copy
Edit
python manage.py runserver
7. Access the Application
Open your browser and go to:

cpp
Copy
Edit
http://127.0.0.1:8000/
✅ Usage
Navigate to the home page to upload or view customer segmentation.

Visualizations display segmented customer groups.

Analyze clusters for marketing insights.

